Zambia’s Lingela Says Barrick Decision May Be Made Within Days

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-05-18T14:09:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/zambian-regulator-says-decision-on-barrick-gold-may-be-made-within-days.html
While Zambia’s Competition and
Consumer Protection Commission has 90 days by law to make a
decision on whether to permit  Barrick Gold Corp. (ABX) ’s takeover of
the Lumwana copper mine through its acquisition of Equinox Gold
Ltd., a decision may be made within days, Brian Lingela a
spokesman for the commission, said in an interview.  Earlier Lingela said the decision would be made within
three months.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  